Lastly, using the equation in Step 4, the net present value is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{NPV}&=\$15,205,189.54-\$14,900,000\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$305,189.54}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the net present value of the project is $305,189.54.

Using the equation in Step 4, the net present value at Year 1 is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{NPV}&=\$13,844,940-\$14,900,000\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{(\$1,055,060)}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the net present value of the project is ($1,055,060) if the project is abandoned at Year 1.

Using the equation in Step 4, the net present value at Year 2 is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{NPV}&=\$15,260,527-\$14,900,000\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$360,527}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the net present value of the project is $360,527 if the project is abandoned at Year 2.

Using the equation in Step 4, the net present value at Year 3 is solved below: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{NPV}&=\$16,186,382.80-\$14,900,000\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$1,286,382.80}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore, the net present value of the project is $1,286,382.80 if the project is abandoned in Year 3.
